# Vercel deploys only web/ (project Root Directory = web). Everything else at
# the repo root is excluded — it's not part of the build, and some of it must
# never be uploaded:
#   - .claude holds an un-gitignored .env.local.bak (secrets)
#   - sdks/python has permission-locked pytest temp dirs that break the scan
#
# NOTE: this is a DENYLIST on purpose. Vercel's uploader prunes ignored
# directories, so an allowlist (`/*` + `!/web`) prunes web/ and fails with
# "Root Directory web does not exist". Don't "simplify" it back to a negation.
/.claude
/.firebase-config
/.firebaserc
/.github
/.pytest_cache
/agent
/api-test
/cli
/dev
/docs
/examples
/functions
/icons
/infra
/load-tests
/monitoring
/scripts
/sdks
/site
/storage
/test-infra
/test-results
*.log
/nul
